-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fuber-ceo-dara-khosrowshahi-takes-a-bus-ride-during-his-india-visit-124022300008_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fuber-ceo-dara-khosrowshahi-takes-a-bus-ride-during-his-india-visit-124022300008_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Heat%20Island%20Effect%20Can%20Make%20Core%20Of%20Cities%207%20Degrees%20Hotter%3A%20Expert%20To%20NDTV%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20heat%20waves%20increase%20in%20India%20with%20the%20rise%20in%20global%20warming%2C%20cities%20are%20particularly%20vulnerable%20because%20temperatures%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20urban%20jungles%20can%20be%20as%20many%20as%20seven%20degrees%20higher%20than%20the%20areas%20surrounding%20them%2C%20a%20leading%20expert%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20exclusively%20to%20NDTV%20on%20Thursday%2C%20Robert%20Muir-Wood%2C%20Chief%20Research%20Officer%20at%20Moody's%20RMS%20-%20a%20risk%20management%20company%20-%20attributed%20this%20rise%20to%20a%20phenomenon%20called%20the%20urban%20heat%20island%20effect%20which%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20not%20only%20detrimental%20to%20productivity%20but%20can%20also%20cause%20illness.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHeat%20deaths%20have%20risen%20in%20India%20in%20the%20past%20decade%20and%2C%20while%20all%20metropolises%20are%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20heat%20island%20effect%2C%20the%20problem%20is%20more%20acute%20in%20India%2C%20where%20cities%20like%20Mumbai%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Chennai%20and%20Kolkata%20have%20a%20very%20high%20population%20density.%20Vanishing%20greenery%20in%20the%20cities%20has%20exacerbated%20the%20problem%2C%20which%20is%20likely%20to%20get%20worse%20as%20almost%2060%25%20of%20the%20global%20population%20will%20be%20living%20in%20urban%20centres%20in%20the%20next%2020%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%2C%20however%2C%20is%20that%20steps%20can%20be%20taken%20to%20mitigate%20the%20heating%20effect%2C%20said%20Mr%20Muir-Wood%2C%20adding%20that%20what's%20needed%20is%20a%20strong%20city%20administration%20that%20is%20committed%20to%20addressing%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHealth%20Dangers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EListing%20the%20main%20causes%20of%20the%20heat%20island%20effect%2C%20Mr%20Muir-Wood%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSo%20there%20are%20three%20drivers%2C%20the%20first%20reason%20is%20that%20the%20surfaces%20of%20the%20buildings%2C%20the%20surfaces%20of%20the%20roads%20absorb%20a%20lot%20of%20heat.%20They%20tend%20to%20be%20dark%20materials.%20They%20may%20be%20glass%20and%20concrete%2C%20but%20they%20absorb%20a%20lot%20of%20heat.%20The%20second%20reason%20is%20that%20there%20are%20lower%20wind%20speeds%20inside%20a%20metropolitan%20area%20where%20you%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20big%20buildings.%20The%20bigger%20the%20buildings%2C%20the%20more%20they%20are%20slowing%20down%20the%20wind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20third%20factor%20is%20that%20there%20will%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20air%20conditioning%20plants%20and%20other%20machinery%2C%20and%20cars%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20city%2C%20and%20they%20are%20all%20producing%20heat%20too.%20Depending%20on%20how%20concentrated%20the%20population%20of%20buildings%20is%2C%20it%20can%20drive%20up%20the%20temperatures%20by%20five%2C%20six%20or%20seven%20degrees%20centigrade%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20city%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPointing%20out%20that%20the%20difference%20is%20the%20highest%20in%20the%20late%20afternoons%2C%20the%20research%20officer%20said%20the%20temperatures%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20city%20can%20be%20dangerous%20to%20health%20and%20also%20reduce%20productivity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20dangerous%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20the%20benefit%20of%20air%20conditioning%2C%20(like%20in)%20a%20factory%20or%20a%20building%20site.%20In%20India%2C%20the%20heat%20wave%20period%20may%20start%20in%20March%20and%20run%20through%20to%20August.%20We%20know%20that%20heat%20waves%20are%20getting%20more%20intense.%20They%20are%20lasting%20longer.%20They%20are%20coming%20earlier.%20And%20we%20know%20the%20temperatures%20are%20reaching%20the%20levels%20at%20which%20they%20can%20be%20dangerous%20to%20health%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20warned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Muir-Wood%20said%20the%20wet%20bulb%20temperature%2C%20which%20also%20takes%20humidity%20into%20consideration%2C%20can%20be%20dangerous%20if%20it%20gets%20close%20to%20the%20natural%20temperature%20of%20a%20human%20being.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Not%20That%20Expensive%20to%20Act'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20a%20question%20on%20how%20the%20urban%20heat%20island%20effect%20can%20be%20mitigated%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20developing%20world%2C%20and%20the%20kind%20of%20investment%20doing%20so%20would%20require%2C%20the%20research%20officer%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20it%20is%20so%20very%20expensive%20to%20take%20action%20to%20get%20on%20top%20of%20the%20problem.%20Some%20cities%20are%20much%20better%20than%20others.%20Cities%20which%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20green%20space%20within%20them%2C%20including%20parks%20and%20trees%2C%20have%20lower%20temperatures.%20I%20think%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20there%20are%20actions%20being%20taken%20currently%2C%20there%20are%20attempts%20to%20open%20up%20lakes.%20I%20think%20there's%20talk%20about%20converting%20the%20racecourse%20into%20a%20park%20and%20into%20a%20forest%2C%20even.%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trouble%2C%20Mr%20Muir-Wood%20said%2C%20is%20that%20a%20lot%20more%20money%20can%20be%20made%20by%20making%20a%20building%20on%20a%20piece%20of%20land%20than%20planting%20trees%20on%20it.%20And%20this%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20where%20a%20strong%20city%20administration%20can%20step%20in%20to%20ensure%20that%20action%20is%20being%20taken%20to%20bring%20down%20temperatures%20for%20everyone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20know%20what%20to%20do.%20It%20is%20not%20that%20expensive%2C%20but%20it%20requires%20a%20quite%20strong%20city%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'It%20Will%20Be%20Impossible%20To%20Work%20Outside'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20how%20realistic%20it%20is%20to%20reduce%20the%20heating%20of%20cities%20when%20urbanisation%20is%20going%20to%20go%20up%2C%20Mr%20Muir-Wood%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20not%20only%20possible%2C%20it%20is%20really%20important.%20Because%20temperatures%20are%20rising%20and%20we%20can%20measure%20those%20increases%20already.%20We%20know%20already%20there%20is%20evidence%20of%20an%20increase%20in%20heat%20deaths%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20compared%20to%20the%20decade%20before.%20So%20this%20is%20important%2C%20important%20stuff.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20actions%20that%20can%20be%20taken%20and%20those%20actions%20are%20really%20important.%20And%20they%20simply%20require%20strong%20planning%20and%20organisation%20in%20cities.%20If%20you%20take%20no%20action%2C%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20city%20will%20get%20hotter%20and%20hotter.%20It%20will%20become%20impossible%20to%20work%20outside%20through%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20day%20because%20the%20temperatures%20will%20be%20dangerously%20high.%20We%20use%20our%20risk%20modelling%20to%20look%20out%20into%20the%20future.%20We%20do%20that%20in%20order%20to%20provide%20the%20information%20that%20people%20need%20to%20take%20action%20today%20to%20prevent%20the%20worst%2C%20the%20most%20dangerous%2C%20increases%20of%20temperature%20actually%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708627560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F5ruq5rso_robert-muirwood-moodys_625x300_22_February_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fheat-island-effect-can-make-core-of-cities-7-degrees-hotter-expert-to-ndtv-5108